fter commissioning. The order was booked in the\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6617704,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.ocean-energy-systems.org/ocean-energy-in-the-world/spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"OES | Country info | Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"These projects are expected to be completed by 2026. ... This initiative aims to adapt Spanish ports for the deployment of offshore wind and marine energy in\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6211049,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.iberdrolaespana.com/press-room/news/detail/210216_np_02_primer_parque_eolico_marino_flotante\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Iberdrola plans first industrial-scale floating offshore wind farm ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The study, design and engineering could begin this year and it could generate more than 2,800 jobs per year until it becomes operational in 2026\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.60245985,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://windar-renovables.com/en/the-offshore-wind-farm-first-tower-to-be-built-in-aviles/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"The offshore wind farm first tower to be built in Avilés\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Windar's plant in Avilés will manufacture the offshore wind farm first tower to be built in Spain. This was announced yesterday by Gamesa in a press release.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.49436116,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.review-energy.com/eolico/construction-begins-on-the-second-largest-offshore-wind-farm-in-the-world\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Construction begins on the second largest offshore wind ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Iberdrola has started the construction of East Anglia THREE, its largest offshore wind farm to date and the second largest in the world.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.4549328,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/press-room/news/detail/Iberdrola-receives-planning-approval-for-Windanker-offshore-wind-farm\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Iberdrola receives planning approval for Windanker ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Share: * Share in Twitter. Share in Twitter. * Share in Facebook. Share in Facebook. The wind farm will have an installed capacity of 315 megawatts (MW), which corresponds to the supply of 315,000 households, and will go into operation in 2026. Windanker is the third of three major offshore projects of the company in Germany and has an investment volume of 1 billion euros. { \\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"NewsArticle\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"headline\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Iberdrola receives planning approval for Windanker offshore wind farm\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Windanker, Iberdrola's third offshore project in the German Baltic Sea, has received approval from the Federal Maritime and Hydrographic Agency (BSH).\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"image\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/documents/20125/5102002/Parque-eoolico-marino-Wikinger-726x484.jpg\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"datePublished\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"01.04.2025 - 14:04 UTC +02:00\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"dateModified\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"01.04.2025 - 14:04 UTC +02:00\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"mainEntityOfPage\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/press-room/news/detail/Iberdrola-receives-planning-approval-for-Windanker-offshore-wind-farm\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"publisher\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Organization\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Iberdrola\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"logo\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"ImageObject\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/documents/20125/4419331/Logo1-iberdrola-363x205.jpg\\\\\\\" } } }\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.32620755,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.rechargenews.com/wind/spain-risks-turning-offshore-wind-opportunity-into-an-own-goal-industry-body-warns/2-1-1847097\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Spain risks turning offshore wind opportunity into an own- ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Spanish industry associations have pleaded with the government in Madrid to launch a long-delayed first offshore wind tender, warning that\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.31782892,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.miteco.gob.es/content/dam/miteco/es/ministerio/planes-estrategias/desarrollo-eolica-marina-energias/enhreolicamarina-pdf_accesible_tcm30-538999.pdf\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Roadmap offshore wind and marine energy in Spain.\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Thus, the Offshore Wind and Marine Energy Roadmap has a four-fold objective: Establish Spain as a European reference hub for technological development and R&D&I for the design, upscaling and demonstration of new technologies, taking advantage of the country’s unique geographical features and maritime regimes, reinforcing the network of test platforms, deploying a “plug & play” enabling framework that aims to become the most agile in the European environment for the testing of new prototypes, and activating at least 200 million euros in public support for technological innovation in the period 2021-2023; \\\\u0007 To be an international and European benchmark in industrial capacities and in the whole value chain of these energies, contributing to European industrial leadership in this field, developing capacities to take advantage of employment opportunities, and generating value chains throughout the life cycle with a Circular Economy perspective; 4 ’An International Vision for Marine ener[...]ng a good environmental status.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.2876532,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://windeurope.org/news/wind-energy-permitting-is-improving-but-governments-still-have-work-to-do/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still have work to do Home News Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still have work to do ## Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still have work to do Europe approved significantly more permits for new onshore wind farms in 202