{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"91b732f9-9f0c-43f4-95e5-25e6b7d6a083","ts":"2025-10-19T15:47:32.417+02:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"142","nodeName":"groq-openai-120b2","workflowName":"graph-knowledge-agent","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq","workflowId":"aS5r9ljDR7IaUyFE","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"System: # ROLE\\n\\nYou are a **Research Agent** with access to **Tavily Search** (search results) and **Fetch** (full page). Your mission is to discover **permits, approvals, grants, subsidies, and financing events** for **utility-scale solar and wind farms scheduled to start construction in 2026**.\\n\\n# BEHAVIOR\\n\\n* The **geographic area** of interest will be provided by the user.\\n* Run up to **5 Tavily searches**. After each search, review the snippets.\\n* When a result looks relevant or promising, **call Fetch** on the page to read the full content.\\n* Use varied angles: government approvals, regulatory filings, EIAs, planning consents, grid connection approvals, auctions/tenders, developer press releases, financial closes, loans, grants/subsidies.\\n* Prefer **official and primary sources** (regulators, government gazettes, banks, developers).\\n* Deduplicate projects by name/country; merge evidence from multiple sources.\\n* Exclude vague announcements that don’t specify **2026 construction start**.\\n\\n# MOST IMPORTANT INFO TO COLLECT PER PROJECT\\n\\n* **Project identity**: name, developer/owner, location (country, region, site).\\n* **Technology**: solar PV, CSP, onshore wind, offshore wind, or hybrid.\\n* **Capacity**: announced or approved MW size.\\n* **Construction schedule**: explicit evidence of 2026 start (quote, phrasing, or official document).\\n* **Permits & approvals**: EIA, planning consent, grid connection approval, other regulatory milestones.\\n* **Grants & subsidies**: public programs, awarded auctions/tenders, subsidy amounts.\\n* **Financing**: loans, bonds, equity investments, financial close announcements (amount, lender/investor, status).\\n* **Notable contractors**: EPC, turbine supplier, or technology provider if named.\\n* **Source details**: title, publisher, URL, publication date.\\n* **Confidence level**: how strong the evidence is (official vs media vs rumor).\\nHuman: Spain\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"2026 construction start solar farm Spain permit approved 2025\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Construction of a 200 MW solar farm in Spain's Andalusia region began in 2025, with operations starting in 2026. The project received necessary permits in 2025.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.eni.com/en-IT/media/press-release/2025/07/plenitude-begins-construction-new-200-mw-solar-park-spain.html\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude begins construction of a new 200 MW solar park ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Entrenúcleos project, located between Dos Hermanas and Coria del Río (Seville, Andalusia), is expected to begin operations in 2026 and generate more than\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.68798697,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.blackridgeresearch.com/blog/top-new-upcoming-europe-renewable-projects?srsltid=AfmBOorvoUleXSa0-yp5LX-e7J5-Oh8OQ6igcDMdbYc8M77yj1O6ARxf\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Top 10 New Upcoming Europe Renewable Projects in 2025\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Zaragoza & Teruel Solar Farm is being planned in the Zaragoza & Teruel provinces, Aragón region, Spain. It is being developed by Bruc Iberia\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6188962,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://solarin.es/solar-incentives-in-spain-2025/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Solar Incentives in Spain 2025 - Solarin\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Deadline to apply: Applications are open until February 27, 2026. Where to apply: Through the official platform of the Generalitat Valenciana. Click here. 2\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.60917604,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"ht