-looking statements. Except as required by law, Q ENERGY does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events or otherwise.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.3403322,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://qenergy.eu/media/detail/q-energy-expands-iberian-footprint-with-a-252-mw-hybrid-solar-portfolio/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Q ENERGY Expands Iberian Footprint with a 252 MW ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"• Q ENERGY's first IPP projects in Iberia with 10-year PPAs **Berlin/Madrid, 2 September 2025.** Q ENERGY has achieved debt financial close on “Taurus B”, a portfolio of seven solar PV plants in Spain with a total capacity of 251.71 MWp. Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group and BNP Paribas were lead arrangers on the financing. Q ENERGY is Europe's provider of holistic solutions for green power plants. The company is active along the entire value chain of renewable energy projects - from solar parks, onshore and offshore wind projects to energy storage solutions and hybrid power plants. Among other things, the quotations from management in this press release and Q ENERGY’s operations and business outlook, contain forward-looking statements.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.15886505,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://strategicenergy.eu/dos-grados-iberia-2026-solar/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Two Degrees strengthens its presence in Iberia with the ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Tordesillas acquisition is part of an ambitious €200 million investment program projected until 2025 or 2026, which includes expanding its\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.06886879,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://zelestra.energy/zelestra-expands-clean-energy-partnership-with-graphic-packaging-international-to-add-further-renewable-electricity-generation-capacity-to-the-european-grid/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Zelestra expands clean energy partnership with Graphic ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"We value your privacy We use essential cookies to make our site work. With your consent, we may also use non-essential cookies to improve user experience, personalize content, personalize ads, and analyze website traffic. For these reasons, we may share your site usage data with our social media, advertising and analytics partners. By clicking “Accept”, you agree to our website's use of cookies as described in our Cookie Policy. You can change your cookie settings at any time by clicking “Preferences”. * What We Value Having a third vPPA in the portfolio makes our supply more resilient by redistributing the original contracted Guarantees of Origin across three plants versus the original two and could support future growth.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.028309563,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.56,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"0d14ccc0-fd8a-43ac-8199-64a9f54a00f3\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"2026 construction start offshore wind farm Spain 2026 permit\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Construction of the offshore wind farm in Spain is set to start in 2026. Permits have been requested for multiple projects, including a 300 MW and a 760MW wind farm. GE Vernova will supply turbines for the 760MW project.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.offshorewind.biz/2021/06/07/iberdrola-requests-permits-for-two-offshore-wind-farms-in-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Iberdrola Requests Permits for Two Offshore Wind Farms in ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The first, 300 MW project is anticipated to be operational in 2026, until when it could create 2,800 jobs per year and involve 66 technology\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7216064,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.windpowermonthly.com/article/1874594/ge-vernova-supply-turbines-760mw-wind-farm-spain\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"GE Vernova to supply turbines for 760MW wind farm in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The wind farm is due online in 2026. GE Vernova will also service the turbines for 15 years after commissioning. The order was booked in the\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6617704,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.ocean-energy-systems.org/ocean-energy-in-the-world/spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"OES | Country info | Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"These projects are expected to be completed by 2026. ... This initiative aims to adapt Spanish ports for the deployment of offshore wind and marine energy in\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6211049,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.iberdrolaespana.com/press-room/news/detail/210216_np_02_primer_parque_eolico_marino_flotante\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Iberdrola plans first industrial-scale floating offshore wind farm ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The study, design and engineering could begin this year and it could generate more than 2,800 jobs per year until it becomes operational in 2026\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.60245985,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://windar-renovables.com/en/the-offshore-wind-farm-first-tower-to-be-built-in-aviles/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"The offshore wind farm first tower to be built in Avilés\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Windar's plant in Avilés will manufacture the offshore wind farm first tower to be built in Spain. This was announced yesterday by Gamesa in a press release.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.49436116,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.review-energy.com/eolico/construction-begins-on-the-second-largest-offshore-wind-farm-in-the-world\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Construction begins on the second largest offshore wind ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Iberdrola has started the construction of East Anglia THREE, its largest offshore wind farm to date and the second largest in the world.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.4549328,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/press-room/news/detail/Iberdrola-receives-planning-approval-for-Windanker-offshore-wind-farm\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Iberdrola receives planning approval for Windanker ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Share: * Share in Twitter. Share in Twitter. * Share in Facebook. Share in Facebook. The wind farm will have an installed capacity of 315 megawatts (MW), which corresponds to the supply of 315,000 households, and will go into operation in 2026. Windanker is the third of three major offshore projects of the company in Germany and has an investment volume of 1 billion euros. { \\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"NewsArticle\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"headline\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Iberdrola receives planning approval for Windanker offshore wind farm\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Windanker, Iberdrola's third offshore project in the German Baltic Sea, has received approval from the Federal Maritime and Hydrographic Agency (BSH).\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"image\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/documents/20125/5102002/Parque-eoolico-marino-Wikinger-726x484.jpg\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"datePublished\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"01.04.2025 - 14:04 UTC +02:00\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"dateModified\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"01.04.2025 - 14:04 UTC +02:00\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"mainEntityOfPage\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/press-room/news/detail/Iberdrola-receives-planning-approval-for-Windanker-offshore-wind-farm\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"publisher\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Organization\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Iberdrola\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"logo\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"ImageObject\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"https://www.iberdrola.com/documents/20125/4419331/Logo1-iberdrola-363x205.jpg\\\\\\\" } } }\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.32620755,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.rechargenews.com/wind/spain-risks-turning-offshore-wind-opportunity-into-an-own-goal-industry-body-warns/2-1-1847097\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Spain risks turning offshore wind opportunity into an own- ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Spanish industry associations have pleaded with the government in Madrid to launch a long-delayed first offshore wind tender, warning that\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.31782892,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.miteco.gob.es/content/dam/miteco/es/ministerio/planes-estrategias/desarrollo-eolica-marina-energias/enhreolicamarina-pdf_accesible_tcm30-538999.pdf\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Roadmap offshore wind and marine energy in Spain.\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Thus, the Offshore Wind and Marine Energy Roadmap has a four-fold objective: Establish Spain as a European reference hub for technological development and R&D&I for the design, upscaling and demonstration of new technologies, taking advantage of the country’s unique geographical features and maritime regimes, reinforcing the network of test platforms, deploying a “plug & play” enabling framework that aims to become the most agile in the European environment for the testing of new prototypes, and activating at least 200 million euros in public support for technological innovation in the period 2021-2023; \\\\u0007 To be an international and European benchmark in industrial capacities and in the whole value chain of these energies, contributing to European industrial leadership in this field, developing capacities to take advantage of employment opportunities, and generating value chains throughout the life cycle with a Circular Economy perspective; 4 ’An International Vision for Marine ener[...]ng a good environmental status.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.2876532,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://windeurope.org/news/wind-energy-permitting-is-improving-but-governments-still-have-work-to-do/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still have work to do Home News Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still have work to do ## Wind energy permitting is improving but Governments still have work to do Europe approved significantly more permits for new onshore wind farms in 2023 than in previous years. That said, Europe is still not permitting enough new wind farms to meet its ambitious 2030 targets. Europe has turned a corner on the permitting of new onshore wind farms. The contrast is even more significant when compared to 2017-2019 when less than 2 GW of permits for new projects were handed out on a yearly basis. **Improved permitting rules**\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.1940167,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.19,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"754fdad6-9ed3-4741-852c-8555c25de55c\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: When fetching robots.txt (https://newsroom.ferrovial.com/robots.txt), received status 403 so assuming that autonomous fetching is not allowed, the user can try manually fetching by using the fetch prompt\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"openai/gpt-oss-120b\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"tool_calls\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":66,\"promptTokens\":5450,\"totalTokens\":5516}}}"}}
