A business model based on growth, respect for the environment and improving people's lives.Supply ChainAn agile, flexible and sustainable service network with local suppliers aligned with our values.EcovoltaicsThe photovoltaic plants of now and tomorrow. Minimum environmental impact and maximum social benefit.Sustainability certificationsSustainability indexes and ratings, as well as our certifications.All about sustainabilitySoltec InnovationsA specialized team with the sole objective of innovating against climate change.AuroraWe are committed to emerging companies with technological solutions that help us promote renewable energy.Lab\\\\n\\\\nDiscover Lab\\\\n\\\\nHarnessing smart solar tracking: Advanced algorithms for hail protectionDiscover our whitepaper on how to take advantage of smart solar tracking for hail protection.All about innovationInvestor kitWhy invest in Soltec?Stock InformationInvestor CalendarFinancial informationAnnual reportsQuarterly financial informationPresentationsNotifications sent to CNMVCorporate governanceBoard of DirectorsGeneral Shareholders ́ MeetingCorporate regulations and policiesAnnual reportsAll about shareholders and investors\\\\n\\\\n* Home\\\\n* Press Room\\\\n* New\\\\n2 July 2025\\\\n# TotalEnergies and Soltec begin the construction of two new solar parks in the Region of Murcia\\\\n\\\\nMurcia, July 22nd, 2025 – TotalEnergies, a global integrated energy company, and Soltec, a firm specialized in solar power solutions, presented today in Murcia the Luminora Solar Dos and Luminora Solar Tres projects at a reception to highlight the beginning of the construction tasks at these facilities. Located in the municipalities of Murcia, San Javier, and San Pedro del Pinatar, Luminora Solar Dos has a total installed capacity of 220 MW. Luminora Solar Tres is located in the municipalities of Murcia and Torre Pacheco and will have 95 MW. The completion of the works is scheduled for October 2026.\\\\n\\\\nWith more than 494,000 bifacial solar panels and solar tracking technology, the two plants will produce 630 GWh of renewable electricity per year, equivalent to the consumption of 180,000 Spanish households. This energy represents a saving of 314,000 tons of CO\\\\\\\\_2 emissions into the atmosphere. Both parks cover 460 hectares and involve an investment of 212 million euros. They also boost job creation in the area, prioritizing the hiring of local employees and suppliers.\\\\n\\\\nDuring the processing, development, construction, and operation phases, it is estimated that 800 direct and indirect jobs will be generated.\\\\n\\\\nIn total, the joint portfolio of TotalEnergies with Soltec amounts to fourteen projects. Four are already in operation (La Asomada, Los Valientes I and II, and La Isla) and six are under construction (Romeral I and II, as well as the two installations presented today, plus Fuente Álamo I and II, which will also begin construction this month). This portfolio of projects has a total capacity of 439 MW, of which 23 MW are already in operation, injecting energy into the grid. Another 356 MW are under construction. An additional 60 MW are still under development.\\\\n\\\\nJordi Torres, General Manager of TotalEnergies Renewables in Spain, stated that “the new projects demonstrate TotalEnergies’ commitment to the energy transition in Spain, a priority country for the Company. Additionally, this announcement and the recent commissioning of our 14 MW park in Los Valientes position us as a key player in the energy transition of the Region of Murcia. They also contribute to TotalEnergies’ global goal of reaching 100 GW installed by 2030”.\\\\n\\\\nMariano Berges, CEO of Soltec, stated: “At Soltec, we work to strengthen our bond with Spain and, particularly, with the Region of Murcia, our place of origin. These projects are a testament to it, and are also a milestone for our company, since they are the last in which we will be the EPC providers. From now on, Soltec is focused in solar trackers supply, a field in which we intend to remain a global leader.”\\\\n\\\\nPresence of TotalEnergies and Soltec in the Región de Murcia\\\\n\\\\nTotalEnergies promotes with Soltec a solar photovoltaic por\\\\n\\\\n<error>Content truncated. Call the fetch tool with a start_index of 5000 to get more content.</error>\\\"}]\\nAI: I will fetch the markdown from the second url.\\nTool: When fetching robots.txt (https://renewablesnow.com/robots.txt), received status 403 so assuming that autonomous fetching is not allowed, the user can try manually fetching by using the fetch prompt\\nAI: I will fetch the markdown from the third url.\\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://www.gem.wiki/Luminora_solar_farm:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nLuminora solar farm - Global Energy Monitor\\\\n\\\\n* Log in\\\\nPageDiscussionView sourceView history\\\\n# Luminora solar farm\\\\n\\\\nFrom Global Energy MonitorJump to:navigation, search\\\\n\\\\n| This article is part of the Global Solar Power Tracker, a Global Energy Monitor project. |\\\\n| --- |\\\\n| Report an error |\\\\n\\\\nLuminora solar farm (Planta solar fotovoltaica Luminora Solar) is a solar photovoltaic (PV) farm in pre-construction in Murcia, Region of Murcia, Spain.\\\\n\\\\n## Project Details\\\\n\\\\n#### Table 1: Phase-level project details for Luminora solar farm\\\\n\\\\n| Phase name | Status | Nameplate capacity | Technology | Owner | Operator |\\\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\\\\n| 2 | Pre-construction^[1] | 196.6 MWac^[2] | PV^[3] | TotalEnergies SE [65%]; Soltec Energias Renovables SL [35%]^[4] | Luminora Solar Dos^[2] |\\\\n| 3 | Pre-construction^[5] | 90 MW^[5] | PV^[5] | Soltec Energias Renovables SL^[5] | – |\\\\n\\\\nRead more about Solar capacity ratings.\\\\n\\\\n## Location\\\\n\\\\n#### Table 2: Phase-level location details for Luminora solar farm\\\\n\\\\n| Phase Name | Location | Coordinates (WGS 84) |\\\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\\\n| 2 | Murcia, Murcia, Region of M